com.apriori.collections

Interface SharedCapacityDequeFactory.CloseableQueue<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of element contained in the queue
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Collection<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Queue<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SharedCapacityDequeFactory.CloseableBlockingDeque<T>, SharedCapacityDequeFactory.CloseableBlockingQueue<T>, SharedCapacityDequeFactory.CloseableDeque<T>
    Enclosing class:
    SharedCapacityDequeFactory

    public static interface SharedCapacityDequeFactory.CloseableQueue<T>
extends java.util.Queue<T>
    A Queue that can be closed. Closing the queue means it can no longer be used. Its share of the total capacity is immediately reclaimed so other queues created by the same factory can use it.

    • Method Summary

        void close()
